<div id="review_1713491310" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1713491310" />
    <a title="Imi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3126915-imi"><img alt="Imi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1457797201p2/3126915.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1713491310?book_show_action=true">Mar 12, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Imi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Imi" href="/user/show/3126915-imi">Imi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780755348558" href="/book/show/6438479-of-bees-and-mist">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3126915-imi?shelf=chinese">chinese</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3126915-imi?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3126915-imi?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3126915-imi?shelf=read-in-2017">read-in-2017</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3126915-imi?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3126915-imi?shelf=kindle">kindle</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3126915-imi?shelf=magical-realism">magical-realism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3126915-imi?shelf=authors-of-colour">authors-of-colour</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3126915-imi?shelf=indonesian">indonesian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3126915-imi?shelf=family-dynamics">family-dynamics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1713491310" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2142318169116129134">I don&apos;t think it is going to be easy to review this without giving too much away, because most of what I didn&apos;t like about it is to do with the direction of the plot in the second half. I was really enjoying the whimsical nature and magical realism of the first half, but in the second it turns into this petty, repetitive family drama, pretty much all &quot;he said, she said&quot;. I couldn&apos;t stand the negativity of all the characters, even those we&apos;re clearly meant to be rooting for. I&apos;m quite honestly ba</span>
  <span id="freeText2142318169116129134" style="display:none">I don't think it is going to be easy to review this without giving too much away, because most of what I didn't like about it is to do with the direction of the plot in the second half. I was really enjoying the whimsical nature and magical realism of the first half, but in the second it turns into this petty, repetitive family drama, pretty much all "he said, she said". I couldn't stand the negativity of all the characters, even those we're clearly meant to be rooting for. I'm quite honestly baffled by a lot characterisation and the decisions made by the characters. And actually some of the author's treatment of certain characters made be feel downright uncomfortable. For example, <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[vilifying Ahab the "foreigner" as some kind of monster, and the terrible one-sided depiction of Eva the monster-in-law <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>. I'm really disappointed that this book turned out to be so hateful, as it seemed to have all the elements I was looking for, in particular, escapist, lyrical magical realism and a focus on strong female characters. Unfortunately, this is not a book I can recommend.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2142318169116129134" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


