<span id="freeTextContainer17220399849526773939">I had heard some really enthusiastic things about this book which made me want to read it, but I couldn&apos;t get past the first 50 pages. The parts I read were drowning in purple prose and there was a huge lack of a plot. Nothing was happening and it was just really boring. <br/><br/>The cover is nice and it made me want to buy it (along with all the positive comments I had heard), but the book went nowhere fast and it felt like reading high school poetry in parts. I could feel that the author was setting up</span>
  <span id="freeText17220399849526773939" style="display:none">I had heard some really enthusiastic things about this book which made me want to read it, but I couldn't get past the first 50 pages. The parts I read were drowning in purple prose and there was a huge lack of a plot. Nothing was happening and it was just really boring. <br /><br />The cover is nice and it made me want to buy it (along with all the positive comments I had heard), but the book went nowhere fast and it felt like reading high school poetry in parts. I could feel that the author was setting up the story but it just took much too long and was really drawn out. Pacing-wise, this is just too slow for me. <br /><br />Maybe I will try to pick it up again one day. Maybe. <br /></span>
